history.content:
For the purpose of software engineering internships, 170 and 161 are definitely the better picks to take in Fall. Taking 170 is always helpful in solving interview coding problems because it teaches you to approach problems in a certain way and gives you exposure to programming paradigms such as Dynamic Programming and Divide & Conquer, while 161 is just a good class for a broad overview of security concepts (which is essential in industry).

On the other hand, 188 & 189 tend to not be that useful for most people in software engineering, unless you're doing something ML-related (the presence of such opportunities for undergrads is extremely limited).
